ACORN SQUASH STUFFED W/ HEARTS OF PALM RICE 🍚  this can be made in under 20 minutes + you can add protein, too! Ingredients from @traderjoes 
Comment below if you’d make this or if you want me to share more recipes! 

INGREDIENTS:
•acorn squash or any other squash 
•package of hearts of palm rice
•chopped veggies of choice (I used cherry tomatoes, zucchini, mushrooms, and onion)
•Buffalo sauce (optional)
•Salt and pepper 

HOW TO MAKE:
1. Slide squash in half and scoop out seeds 
2. Bake in oven at 400 for 20-30 minutes or microwave for 6-8 minutes 
3. Prepare rice by pouring in bowl
4. Chop veggies finely and add to rice bowl
5. Microwave or sauté mixture as directed 
6. Once squash is done, fill squash with rice
7. Top with Buffalo sauce or sauce or choice
